<h2> Welcome to the Sorting Hat's quizz </h2>
<p>To what House do you belong to? </p>

<form method="POST" action="/hatquizz">
    <p>You and two friends need to cross a bridge guarded by a river troll who insists on fighting one of you before he will let all of you pass. Do you:</p>
        <input type="radio" id="eagle" name="animal" value="ravenclaw">
            <label for="eagle">Attempt to confuse the troll into letting all three of you pass without fighting?</label>
        <input type="radio" id="lion" name="animal" value="gryffindor">
            <label for="lion">Volunteer to fight?</label>
        <input type="radio" id="snake" name="animal" value="slytherin">
            <label for="snake">Suggest drawing lots to decide which of you will fight?</label>
         <input type="radio" id="badger" name="animal" value="hufflepuff">
            <label for="badger">Suggest that all three of you should fight (without telling the troll)?</label>

    <p>You enter an enchanted garden. What would you be most curious to examine first?</p>
        <input type="radio" id="garden1" name="garden" value="gryffindor">
            <label for="garden1">The bubbling pool, in the depths of which something luminous is swirling</label>
        <input type="radio" id="garden2" name="garden" value="hufflepuff">
            <label for="garden2">The fat red toadstools that appear to be talking to each other</label>
        <input type="radio" id="garden3" name="garden" value="slytherin">
            <label for="garden3">The silver leafed tree bearing golden apples</label>
        <input type="radio" id="garden4" name="garden" value="ravenclaw">
            <label for="garden4">The status of an old wizard with a strangely twinkled eye</label>

 <!-- From there if needed I'll need to update all the 'id's and the 'for' -->
    <p>After you have died, what would you like people to do when they hear your name?</p>
        <input type="radio" id="lion" name="death" value="gryffindor">
            <label for="lion">Ask for more stories about your adventures</label>
        <input type="radio" id="badger" name="death" value="hufflepuff">
            <label for="badger">Miss you, but smile</label>
        <input type="radio" id="snake" name="death" value="slytherin">
            <label for="snake">Think with admiration of your achievements</label>
        <input type="radio" id="eagle" name="death" value="ravenclaw">
            <label for="eagle">You don't care about what they think of you after you're dead, it's what they think of you while you're alive that matters</label>

    <p>Which road tempts you most?</p>
        <input type="radio" id="eagle" name="road" value="ravenclaw">
            <label for="eagle">The cobbled street lined with ancient buildings</label>
        <input type="radio" id="lion" name="road" value="gryffindor">
            <label for="lion">The twisting, leaf-strewn path through the woods</label>
        <input type="radio" id="snake" name="road" value="slytherin">
            <label for="snake">The narrow, dark, lantern-lit alley</label>
        <input type="radio" id="badger" name="road" value="hufflepuff">
            <label for="badger">The wide, sunny, grassy lane</label>

    <p>Late at night, walking alone down the street, you hear a peculiar cry that you believe to have a magical source. Do you:</p>
        <input type="radio" id="lion" name="night" value="gryffindor">
            <label for="lion">Draw your wand and try to discover the source of the noise?</label>
        <input type="radio" id="badger" name="night" value="hufflepuff">
            <label for="badger">Proceed with caution, keeping an eye on your wand and an eye out for any disturbance?</label>
        <input type="radio" id="snake" name="night" value="slytherin">
            <label for="snake">Withdraw into the shadows to await developments, while mentally reviewing all defensive and offensive spells you know, shoul trouble occur?</label>
        <input type="radio" id="eagle" name="night" value="ravenclaw">
            <label for="eagle">Draw your wand and stand your ground?</label>
</form>

<button onclick="submit_quizz()"> Discover my House </button>



